pageTitle: Lewes Boat Building Program | Lewes Historical Society
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {4525=On Saturday, June 15 from 10:00am-4:00pm, come to The Lewes Lifesaving Station to view wooden boats made by wood boat hobbyists. Also, come to enter for the winning raffle ticket to receive a 12’ Bevin’s Skiff constructed by the Wooden Boat Crew.  The drawing will be at the final Historic Lewes Farmers Market on Saturday, September 28., 5448=Lewes was a shipbuilding town. From the 1600s until the mid 1800s, hundreds of vessels of all sizes were built on Lewes Creek.  Join The Lewes Historical Society as we rekindle this art in Lewes as part of our Family Boat Building Weekend over Fathers’ Day Weekend June 14-16., 3375=Register your group to participate in the 2014 event by calling 302-645-7670; space is limited.}
